<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-25T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-25T03:00:00-05:00" n="560" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13550: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-25T16:00:00+08:00">July 25, 1938—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 25—1:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Shanghai and Tokyo please inform Japanese authorities [that] committee of
                            4 missions including 2 American missions proposes establishment safety
                            zone Ichang, Hupeh, at Catholic Convent 2 kilometers southeast of city
                            on prominent hill. Convent marked with French, Belgian and Red Cross
                            flags. Maps follow. Local British, French, Belgian Consuls also received
                            notification from committee.</p>
                        <p>Sent to Shanghai. Shanghai please repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>